How to build and run the JDOS batch scheduler 

1. Build
   cd volcano.sh/volcano
   make vc-scheduler
   make verify
   make unit-test
2. Deploy the queue and podgroup CRDs, and create a default queue (default-queue)
   cd volcano.sh/volcano/example/jdos
   deploy.sh
4. Start the scheduler (scheduler name: jdos-batch, default queue: default-queue)
   cd volcano.sh/volcano
   ./_output/bin/vc-scheduler --master=http://exp-k8s-api.jd.com --schedule-period=5s --v=5 --log-dir=./log --listen-address=:8081 --scheduler-name=jdos-batch --default-queue=default --node-max-tasks=30
5. Summit a job (make sure the cluster has enough resources to start all the pods of the job) 
   cd volcano.sh/volcano/example/jdos
   kubectl apply -f small-job.yaml
6. Check the status
   kubectl get pods
   kubectl get jobs
7  When the job completes, delete the job,podgroup and pods
   cd volcano.sh/volcano/example/jdos
   del-all.sh
